This makes it highly likely that the paper belongs to the cs.DB sub-category. 
2. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): The paper focuses on location-based social networks (LBSNs) and proposes a two-layer hybrid index structure called Network Embedding Time-aware R-tree (NETR-tree) to handle social-based time-aware spatial keyword queries. This makes it highly likely that the paper belongs to the cs.SI sub-category.
